This is multi-cluster ArgoCD — very common in production.

ArgoCD is installed in ONE cluster and manages ALL other clusters:

ArgoCD cluster (management)
  argocd installed here
        │
        ├──── Cluster 1 (dev)
        ├──── Cluster 2 (staging)
        ├──── Cluster 3 (prod-us-east)
        ├──── Cluster 4 (prod-us-west)
        ├──── Cluster 5 (prod-eu)
        ├──── Cluster 6 (prod-ap)
        ├──── Cluster 7 (data)
        ├──── Cluster 8 (ml)
        ├──── Cluster 9 (security)
        └──── Cluster 10 (backup)

One ArgoCD → manages all 10 ✅

How ArgoCD connects to other clusters:

# Step 1 — Login to ArgoCD CLI
argocd login <ARGOCD_SERVER_URL>

# Step 2 — Add each cluster to ArgoCD
argocd cluster add <CONTEXT_NAME>

# For example:
argocd cluster add eks-cluster-dev
argocd cluster add eks-cluster-staging
argocd cluster add eks-cluster-prod-us

# Step 3 — Verify clusters added
argocd cluster list

# Output:
SERVER                                     NAME              STATUS
https://kubernetes.default.svc             in-cluster        Successful
https://eks-dev.us-east-2.amazonaws.com    eks-cluster-dev   Successful
https://eks-stg.us-east-2.amazonaws.com    eks-cluster-stg   Successful
https://eks-prd.us-east-2.amazonaws.com    eks-cluster-prd   Successful

