  project: default
  source:
    repoURL: https://github.com/YOUR_USERNAME/my-argocd-apps
    targetRevision: main
    path: sample-app

  destination:
    server: https://eks-dev.us-east-2.amazonaws.com  # ← specific cluster
    namespace: sample-app

---
apiVersion: argoproj.io/v1alpha1
kind: Application
metadata:
  name: sample-app-prod
  namespace: argocd
spec:
  project: default
  source:
    repoURL: https://github.com/YOUR_USERNAME/my-argocd-apps
    targetRevision: main
    path: sample-app

  destination:
    server: https://eks-prd.us-east-2.amazonaws.com  # ← different cluster
    namespace: sample-app

Two patterns for multi-cluster:

Pattern 1 — Hub and Spoke (what most companies use)

ArgoCD (hub cluster)
                installed here only
                        │
          ┌─────────────┼─────────────┐
          ▼             ▼             ▼
       Dev EKS      Staging EKS    Prod EKS
      (spoke)        (spoke)       (spoke)

ArgoCD NOT installed on spoke clusters
ArgoCD manages them remotely ✅

Pattern 2 — ArgoCD on every cluster

Cluster 1          Cluster 2          Cluster 3
ArgoCD ✅          ArgoCD ✅          ArgoCD ✅
manages itself     manages itself     manages itself

each cluster is independent
more complex to manage ❌
used when clusters are in
different regions/companies

ArgoCD does not care about regions — it just needs the API endpoint:

ArgoCD cluster (us-east-1)
        │
        ├──── EKS us-east-1   (same region)
        ├──── EKS us-west-2   (different region)
        ├──── EKS eu-west-1   (Europe)
        ├──── EKS ap-south-1  (India)
        └──── EKS ap-east-1   (Singapore)

All connected via Kubernetes API endpoint ✅
Region does not matter ✅

How it connects across regions:

ArgoCD talks to each cluster via:
  https://eks-cluster.us-west-2.amazonaws.com   ← API endpoint
  https://eks-cluster.eu-west-1.amazonaws.com   ← API endpoint
  https://eks-cluster.ap-south-1.amazonaws.com  ← API endpoint

Just HTTPS calls over internet
No VPN needed for public endpoints ✅

Hub and Spoke is recommended because:

✅ One place to see all deployments
✅ One place to manage access
✅ One place to set policies
✅ Less resource usage
   (ArgoCD not running on every cluster)
✅ Easier to audit
✅ One UI for everything

Simple summary:

ArgoCD multi-cluster:
  ✅ Install ArgoCD on ONE cluster only
  ✅ Add other clusters via argocd cluster add
  ✅ Each Application points to specific cluster
  ✅ One UI manages all 10 clusters
  ✅ App of Apps pattern scales to any number
  ✅ Projects control who can deploy where

Your company with 10 clusters:
  1 ArgoCD installation
  10 clusters registered
  All managed from one place ✅

